                <p/>      
                
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Philylla.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Philylla.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Philylla.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>About the so-called 'Red Tomb' see commentary at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr007000</ref>.</p>
                <p>This woman's name, not otherwise attested in Cyrenaica, is akin to <foreign xml:lang="grc">Φιλυλλιώ</foreign> known at Cyrene through 
                    <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.126.html">IRCyr2020 C.126</ref> and commented by <bibl><ptr target="#masson1983"/></bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
